-- German Solar Industry to Propose Subsidy Changes, FTD Reports
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-01-19T06:51:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/german-solar-industry-to-propose-subsidy-changes-ftd-reports.html
Germany ’s solar industry is ready to
propose adjustments to subsidies in a meeting with Environment
Minister Norbert Roettgen, the  Financial Times Deutschland 
reported, citing company officials it didn’t identify.  The industry will propose several smaller subsidy cuts a
year instead of two larger ones to reduce installations that
reached a record 7.5 gigawatts last year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
